<p>


<caption align=bottom>*Constant exchange rate (CER) growth represents growth over the combined sales of Glaxo and Wellcome for the year to 31st December 1994 excluding currency movements, calculated as if the exchange rates used to translate the results of overseas companies into sterling had remained unchanged from those used in 1994.</caption>
</table>
<hr>

Pro forma sales by Glaxo Wellcome for the 12 months to 31st December 1995 were &#163;7,973 million, representing an increase of 4% in sterling terms or 3% at CER.  Volume growth was 4%, but pricing pressure had a net 1% adverse effect on sales revenue.<p>

