<h1><font size=7>Mushrooming problems</font></h1>
<hr size=4>
<br>
<h2><font size=6>Responding to the rise of fungal infection</font></h2><br>


<font size=5>The incidence of bloodstream infection by <a
href="fungpix.html"><cite>Candida albicans</cite></a> increased by almost
50% in the last decade, and other fungal fellows are gaining ground as
well. Odyssey surveys the urgent challenges clinicians face as mycoses
proliferate and new resistant strains of fungi develop. </font><p>

by J. Verhoef, I.M. Hoepelman and M. Lipovsky,<br><font size=3>
Eijkman-Winkler Institute of Medical and Clinical Microbiology,<br>
University Hospital Utrecht, the Netherlands<br></font>

