</DOCHDR>
<html><head><title>RasMol Manual: User Colours</title></head><body background="back1.gif" bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#1a1afa" vlink="30aa30"> 
<br clear=left>

<ul><ul><ul><ul><ul><ul><ul type=disc>

<h1><font size=7>RasMol manual</font></h1>
<hr size=4><br>
<h2><font size=6>User Colours</font></h2><p>
The RasMol
<tt><b>user</b></tt>
colour scheme allows RasMol to use the colour scheme stored in the
PDB file. The colours for each atom are stored in COLO records placed
in the PDB data file. This convention was introduced by David Bacon's
Raster3D program.

<p>
<a href="chcolour.html">Colour schemes</a></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul>

</body>
</html>
</DOC>
