<html><head><title>RasMol Manual: Backbone Set</title></head><body background="back1.gif" bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#1a1afa" vlink="30aa30"> 
<br clear=left>

<ul><ul><ul><ul><ul><ul><ul type=disc>

<h1><font size=7>RasMol manual</font></h1>
<hr size=4><br>

<h2><font size=6>Backbone Set</font></h2><p>
This set contains the four atoms of each amino acid that form the
polypeptide N-C-C-O backbone of proteins, and the atoms the sugar
phosphate backbone of nucleic acids.
Use the RasMol predefined sets
<tt><b>protein</b></tt>
and
<tt><b>nucleic</b></tt>
to distinguish between the two forms of backbone.
Atoms in nucleic acids and proteins are either
<tt><b>backbone</b></tt>
or
<a href="sidech.html"><tt><b>sidechain.</b></tt></a>
This set is equivalent to the RasMol expression
"<tt><b>(protein or nucleic) and not sidechain</b></tt>"
<p>
The predefined set
<tt><b>mainchain</b></tt>
is synonymous with the set
<tt><b>backbone.</b></tt>

<p>
<a href="predef.html">Predefined sets</a></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul>

</body>
</html>
</DOC>
