<html><head><title>RasMol Manual: Turn Set</title></head><body background="back1.gif" bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#1a1afa" vlink="30aa30"> <basefont 
<br clear=left>

<ul><ul><ul><ul><ul><ul><ul type=disc>

<h1><font size=7>RasMol manual</font></h1>
<hr size=4><br>
<h2><font size=6>Turn Set</font></h2><p>
This set contains all atoms that form part of a protein turns
as determined by either the PDB file author or Kabsch and
Sander's DSSP algorithm. By default, RasMol uses the secondary
structure determination given in the PDB file if it exists.
Otherwise, it uses the DSSP algorithm as used by the RasMol
<a href="struct.html"><tt><b>structure</b></tt></a>
command.

<p>
<a href="predef.html">Predefined sets</a></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul>

</body>
</html>
</DOC>
