<ul><ul><ul><ul><ul><ul><ul type=disc>

<h1><font size=7>Rasmol Manual</font></h1>
<hr size=4><br>

<h2><font size=6>Alpha Set</font></h2><p>
The set of alpha carbons in the protein molecule. This set is
approximately equivalent to the RasMol atom expression
"<tt><b>*.CA</b></tt>"
This command should not be confused with the predefined set
<a href="helixset.html"><tt><b>helix</b></tt></a>
which contains the atoms in the amino acids of the protein's
alpha helices.

<p>
<a href="predef.html">Predefined sets</a></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul>

</body>
