        <p align="left"><font size="3">The National Union of
        Mineworkers (NUM) was formed in 1982 and represents approximately
        357,000 members in the mining and electrical energy
        industries, the vast majority of the unionised workforce.
        Since its inception, the issues of wages, racial
        discrimination and health and safety have been the pivots
        of its campaigns for improved conditions for mine and
        energy workers. The NUM is the largest recognised
        collective bargaining agent representing workers in the
        mining industry and the electrical energy industry. </font></p>
